<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="complex_number_constructors" id="complex_number_constructors">Complex number constructors</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;complex&gt;</span>
    complex<span class="br0">&#40;</span> T real <span class="sy1">=</span> T<span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span>, T imag <span class="sy1">=</span> T<span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span>
    complex<span class="br0">&#40;</span> complex x <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>

The first constructor creates a complex number from rectangular coordinates. (To create a complex number from polar coordinates, use the <a href="polar" class="wikilink1" title="numeric:complex:polar">polar</a> function.)
The second constructor copies another complex number.

</p>

